<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF84FFCEA7ADFB81FEC2D9BD" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF84FFCEA7ADFB81FEF0D889" blockId="29.[189,310,1134,1160]" box="[189,310,1134,1160]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF84FFCEA7ADFB81FEF0D889" bold="true" box="[189,310,1134,1160]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF84FFCEA7ADFB81FEF0D889" bold="true" box="[189,310,1134,1160]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF84FFCEA7ADFB70FEC2D9BD" blockId="29.[187,1399,1183,1468]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Based in part on 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF84FFCEA69AFB70FDA8D8B8" author="Seiter M. &amp; Schramm F. D. &amp; Schwaha T." box="[394,622,1183,1209]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Seiter" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="349 - 361" part="4438" refId="ref153597" refString="Seiter M., Schramm F. D. &amp; Schwaha T. 2018. Description of a new Charinus species (Amblypygi: Charinidae) from the Monsenor Nouel province, Dominican Republic. Zootaxa 4438: 349 - 361. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4438.2.9" title="Description of a new Charinus species (Amblypygi: Charinidae) from the Monsenor Nouel province, Dominican Republic" type="journal article" year="2018">
Seiter 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF84FFCEA6C8FB4FFDD2D8B8" box="[472,532,1183,1209]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
, this species may be separated from other Caribbean and Central American 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF84FFCEA626FB2BFE65D8DF" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[310,419,1220,1246]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF84FFCEA626FB2BFE65D8DF" box="[310,419,1220,1246]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Charinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by means of the following combination of characters: median eyes absent and lateral eyes reduced; cheliceral claw with 2–4 teeth; female gonopods cushion-like with lateral projections directed posteriorly and unsclerotized; tibia of leg I with 21 or 22 articles, tarsus I with 37 or 38 articles; first tarsal article about five times as long as second article; pedipalp femur with three dorsal spines and two ventral spines; pedipalp patella with three dorsal spines and two ventral spines; leg IV basitibia with three pseudo-articles; leg IV distitibia with 16 trichobothria; trichobothrium 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF84FFCEA327FA92FB95D996" box="[1079,1107,1405,1431]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">bc</emphasis>
situated closer to 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF84FFCEA236FA92FAFBD996" box="[1318,1341,1405,1431]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">bf</emphasis>
than to 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF84FFCEA7CBFA4DFF3BD9BD" box="[219,253,1442,1468]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">sbf</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF84FFCEA7ADFA0AFB21DA2E" box="[189,1255,1509,1584]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF84FFCEA7ADFA0AFE82D9FE" blockId="29.[189,324,1509,1535]" box="[189,324,1509,1535]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF84FFCEA7ADFA0AFE82D9FE" bold="true" box="[189,324,1509,1535]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF84FFCEA7ADFA0AFE82D9FE" bold="true" box="[189,324,1509,1535]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF84FFCEA7ADF9F9FB21DA2E" blockId="29.[189,1255,1557,1584]" box="[189,1255,1557,1584]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Noun in apposition taken from the historical Taíno chiefdom of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF84FFCEA4BBF9FAFB25DA2E" authority="(Seiter et al. 2018)" baseAuthorityName="Seiter" baseAuthorityYear="2018" box="[939,1251,1557,1583]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magua">
Maguá (
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF84FFCEA31CF9FAFB1DDA2E" author="Seiter M. &amp; Schramm F. D. &amp; Schwaha T." box="[1036,1243,1557,1583]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Seiter" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="349 - 361" part="4438" refId="ref153597" refString="Seiter M., Schramm F. D. &amp; Schwaha T. 2018. Description of a new Charinus species (Amblypygi: Charinidae) from the Monsenor Nouel province, Dominican Republic. Zootaxa 4438: 349 - 361. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4438.2.9" title="Description of a new Charinus species (Amblypygi: Charinidae) from the Monsenor Nouel province, Dominican Republic" type="journal article" year="2018">
Seiter 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF84FFCEA349F9F9FB52DA2E" box="[1113,1172,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
